        <name xml:lang="en">phenol</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value based on stoichiometric calculations and literature data. 
94.11304g/mol is the molar mass of phenol (C6H6O). 
206.32808g/mol is the molar mass of 2,4-di-tert-butylphenol (C14H22O). 

2,4-Di-tert-butylphenol can be produced from phenol or 4-tert-butylphenol by alkylation with isobutene under mild reaction conditions and in presence of small amounts of sulfuric acid at temperatures lowe than
80 degree C (Feige et al., 2000). Chemical reaction: 2C4H8 + C6H6O → C14H22O, the assumed conversion efficiency is 0.75.</comment>
